main event: An unidentified object was observed directly overhead in San Francisco, California at approximately 0930 hours on 3 November 1950.
interesting points: The object was bright and larger than an ordinary star., Mr. _____ interviewed stated that he and eight or ten others saw the object disappearing towards the west., The object appeared to be suspended in the sky with no drive mechanism., It was observed for about 20 to 30 seconds at an estimated altitude of approximately 20,000 feet., The object was silver dollar in color, white, and smaller than a medium type jet aircraft.
witness description: Mr. _____ was interviewed along with eight or ten other people.
